# Spring Boot Ultimate Production Rules - Security (10 Rules)

1. Use strong password hashing with BCrypt/Argon2 and rotate policy parameters safely.
2. Never log secrets, credentials, tokens, card data, or personally sensitive payload fields.
3. Enforce authentication and authorization on all non-public endpoints.
4. Use least-privilege RBAC/ABAC policies and deny-by-default security configuration.
5. Validate and sanitize all inputs to reduce SQL injection, XSS, and deserialization risks.
6. Use parameterized queries/ORM bindings exclusively; ban string-concatenated SQL.
7. Store secrets in secure environment stores (vault/K8s secrets), never in source code.
8. Enforce TLS in transit and encryption-at-rest policies for sensitive data.
9. Implement rate limiting and abuse protection on authentication and critical transaction endpoints.
10. Audit security-relevant actions (login, role change, payment action) with immutable logs.
